<p style="Heading 2" xid="2314" props="text-indent:0in; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in"><c props="font-weight:bold">The 802.11 standard</c></p>
<p style="Standard" xid="2315" props="font-size:11pt">The standard we are most interested in is 802.11 as it defines the protocol for Wireless LAN.</p>
<p style="Standard" xid="2316" props="font-size:11pt">The 802.11 Amendments are so numerous they have in the last few years started using 2 letters instead of 1. (802.11z - the DLS amendment -</p>
<p style="Standard" xid="2317" props="font-size:11pt">gave way to 802.11aa, ab, ac..., etc)</p>
<p style="Standard" xid="2318" props="font-size:11pt"><c></c></p>
